  <front>
    <title>Deprecating FFDH Ciphersuites in TLS</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-bartle-tls-deprecate-ffdh-00"/>
    <author initials="C." surname="Bartle" fullname="Carrick Bartle">
      <organization>Apple, Inc.</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="N." surname="Aviram" fullname="Nimrod Aviram"/>
    <author initials="F." surname="Valsorda" fullname="Filippo Valsorda"/>
    <date day="30" month="July" year="2021"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   This document deprecates the use of finite field Diffie Hellman
   cipher suites and discourages the use of elliptic curve Diffie
   Hellman cipher suites, both of which have known vulnerabilities or
   improper security properties when implemented incorrectly.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
